tion of giving it up voluntarily.  Going to take it from me?&quot;<br>
<br>
He drains the tankyard, slams it down, and stands, that cynical little half-smile still on his lips.  &quot;Go ahead, paleskin.  You'll have to beat me bloody to do it, and afterward I'll go for your throat with my bare hands.&quot;  There's a dangerous glint in Severan's eyes.  &quot;You'll have to kill me, you see.  Kill me once and again and forever.&quot;<br>
<br>
He smiles widely, showing teeth.  &quot;And if you <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>do</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> kill me, even if you attack me, you only contribute to the world's violence.  You only feed hate and pain and the gods' desire for blood.  Remember that before you draw your weapon.&quot;<br>
<br>
The dark elf's own sword remains in its sheath. <p>-- Severan, warrior.<br>
